net-snmp provides the SNMP client/manager library and tools, and (with the
"ssl" feature, enabled by default) SNMPv3 (USM auth/privacy) backed by OpenSSL.

Installed layout (standard vcpkg):

    include/net-snmp/net-snmp-config.h
    include/net-snmp/net-snmp-includes.h
    lib/netsnmp.lib

net-snmp does not ship a CMake config package, so link it manually:

    find_path(NETSNMP_INCLUDE_DIR net-snmp/net-snmp-config.h)
    find_library(NETSNMP_LIBRARY NAMES netsnmp)
    target_include_directories(YourTarget PRIVATE ${NETSNMP_INCLUDE_DIR})
    target_link_libraries(YourTarget PRIVATE ${NETSNMP_LIBRARY} ws2_32)

With the "ssl" feature, OpenSSL is linked transitively; if you call the library
directly you may also need OpenSSL::SSL and OpenSSL::Crypto on the link line.

This port targets Windows (MSVC). On other platforms, use the system net-snmp
package (e.g. libsnmp-dev on Debian/Ubuntu, net-snmp via Homebrew).
